051/**
052 * A representation of a domain of valid Java constructs.
053 *
054 * <p>A <dfn id="domain">domain</dfn> is a set of valid Java <a href="#construct">constructs</a>. A {@link Domain}
055 * provides access to a domain and its members.</p>
056 *
057 * <p>A Java <dfn id="construct">construct</dfn> is either a <a href="#type">type</a> or an <a
058 * href="#element">element</a>.</p>
059 *
060 * <p>A <dfn id="type">type</dfn> is a usage of a Java type, most commonly represented as a {@link TypeMirror}.</p>
061 *
062 * <p>An <dfn id="element">element</dfn> ia a declaration of a Java program element, most commonly represented as an
063 * {@link Element}.</p>
064 *
065 * <p>Domains impose constraints on the <a href="#type">types</a> and <a href="#element">elements</a> they contain, and
066 * on the kinds and semantics of operations that can be performed on them.</p>
067 *
068 * <p>This interface is modeled on a deliberately restricted combination of the {@link javax.lang.model.util.Elements}
069 * and {@link javax.lang.model.util.Types} interfaces.</p>
070 *
071 * <p>{@link Domain} implementations must be thread-safe.</p>
072 *
073 * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson" target="_top">Laird Nelson</a>
074 */
075@SuppressWarnings("try")
076public interface Domain {

238  /**
239   * Returns the {@link DeclaredType} {@linkplain TypeElement#asType() of} the supplied {@link TypeElement} with the
240   * supplied {@link TypeMirror} arguments (if any), yielding a parameterized type.
241   *
242   * <p>Given a {@link TypeElement} representing the class named {@link java.util.Set java.util.Set} and a {@link
243   * TypeMirror} representing the type declared by {@link String java.lang.String}, for example, this method will return
244   * a {@link DeclaredType} representing the parameterized type corresponding to {@link java.util.Set
245   * java.util.Set&lt;java.lang.String&gt;}.</p>
246   *
247   * <p>The number of supplied type arguments must either equal the number of the supplied {@link TypeElement}'s
248   * {@linkplain TypeElement#getTypeParameters() formal type parameters}, or must be zero. If it is zero, and if the
249   * supplied {@link TypeElement} {@link #generic(Element) is generic}, then the supplied {@link TypeElement}'s raw type

251   *

253   * be contained within a {@linkplain #generic(Element) generic} outer class. The parameterized type {@code
254   * Outer<String>.Inner<Number>}, for example, may be constructed by first using this method to get the type {@code
255   * Outer<String>}, and then invoking {@link #declaredType(DeclaredType, TypeElement, TypeMirror...)}.</p>

260   *

262   *

267   * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se23/html/jls-4.html#jls-4.5 Java Language Specification, section 4.5

346  /**
347   * A convenience method that returns the <dfn>element type</dfn> of the supplied {@link TypeMirror}.
348   *
349   * <p>The element type of an {@linkplain TypeKind#ARRAY array type} is the element type of its {@linkplain
350   * ArrayType#getComponentType() component type}.</p>.
351   *
352   * <p>The element type of every other kind of type is the type itself. Note that the semantics of the prior sentence
353   * diverge deliberately, primarily for convenience, from those of the relevant section in the Java Language
354   * Specification.</p>
355   *
356   * @param t a {@link TypeMirror}; must not be {@code null}
357   *
358   * @return the <dfn>element type</dfn> of the supplied {@link TypeMirror}; never {@code null}
359   *
360   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code t} is {@code null}
361   *
362   * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se23/html/jls-10.html#jls-10.1 Java Language Specification, section
363   * 10.1
364   */
365  public default TypeMirror elementType(final TypeMirror t) {
366    return switch (t) {
367    case null -> throw new NullPointerException("t");
368    case UniversalType ut -> ut.elementType();
369    default -> {
370      try (var lock = lock()) {
371        yield t.getKind() == TypeKind.ARRAY ? this.elementType(((ArrayType)t).getComponentType()) : t;
372      }
373    }
374    };
375  }

398  /**
399   * A convenience method that returns an {@link ExecutableElement} representing the static initializer, constructor or
400   * method described by the supplied arguments, <strong>or {@code null} if no such {@link ExecutableElement}
401   * exists</strong>.
402   *
403   * @param declaringElement a {@link TypeElement} representing the class that declares the executable; must not be
404   * {@code null}
405   *
406   * @param returnType the {@linkplain ExecutableElement#getReturnType() return type} of the executable; must not be
407   * {@code null}
408   *
409   * @param name the {@linkplain ExecutableElement#getSimpleName() name} of the executable; must not be {@code null}
410   *
411   * @param parameterTypes {@link TypeMirror}s that represent the executable's {@linkplain
412   * ExecutableElement#getParameters() parameter types}
413   *
414   * @return an {@link ExecutableElement} with an {@link ElementKind} of {@link ElementKind#CONSTRUCTOR}, {@link
415   * ElementKind#METHOD}, or {@link ElementKind#STATIC_INIT}, or {@code null}
416   *
417   * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
418   */
419  public default ExecutableElement executableElement(final TypeElement declaringElement,
420                                                     final TypeMirror returnType,
421                                                     final CharSequence name,
422                                                     final TypeMirror... parameterTypes) {
423    return switch (declaringElement) {
424    case null -> throw new NullPointerException("declaringElement");
425    case UniversalElement ue -> {
426      final List<? extends UniversalElement> ees = ue.getEnclosedElements();
427      yield ees.stream()
428        .sequential()
429        .filter(e -> e.getKind().isExecutable() && e.getSimpleName().contentEquals(name))
430        .map(UniversalElement.class::cast)
431        .filter(ee -> {
432            if (!this.sameType(returnType, ee.getReturnType())) {
433              return false;
434            }
435            final List<? extends UniversalElement> ps = ee.getParameters();
436            if (ps.size() != parameterTypes.length) {
437              return false;
438            }
439            for (int i = 0; i < parameterTypes.length; i++) {
440              if (!this.sameType(ps.get(i).asType(), parameterTypes[i])) {
441                return false;
442              }
443            }
444            return true;
445          })
446        .findFirst()
447        .orElse(null);
448    }
449    default -> {
450      try (var lock = this.lock()) {
451        final List<? extends Element> ees = declaringElement.getEnclosedElements();
452        yield ees.stream()
453          .sequential()
454          .filter(e -> e.getKind().isExecutable() && e.getSimpleName().contentEquals(name))
455          .map(ExecutableElement.class::cast)
456          .filter(ee -> {
457              if (!this.sameType(returnType, ee.getReturnType())) {
458                return false;
459              }
460              final List<? extends VariableElement> ps = ee.getParameters();
461              if (ps.size() != parameterTypes.length) {
462                return false;
463              }
464              for (int i = 0; i < parameterTypes.length; i++) {
465                if (!this.sameType(ps.get(i).asType(), parameterTypes[i])) {
466                  return false;
467                }
468              }
469              return true;
470            })
471          .findFirst()
472          .orElse(null);
473      }
474    }
475    };
476  }

478  /**
479   * A convenience method that returns {@code true} if and only if the supplied {@link Element} is <dfn>generic</dfn>.
480   *
481   * @param e an {@link Element}; must not be {@code null}
482   *
483   * @return {@code true} if and only if the supplied {@link Element} is <dfn>generic</dfn>; {@code false} otherwise
484   *
485   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code e} is {@code null}
486   *
487   * @see Parameterizable
488   *
489   * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se23/html/jls-8.html#jls-8.1.2 Java Language Specification, section
490   * 8.1.2
491   *
492   * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se23/html/jls-8.html#jls-8.4.4 Java Language Specification, section
493   * 8.4.4
494   *
495   * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se23/html/jls-8.html#jls-8.8.4 Java Language Specification, section
496   * 8.8.4
497   *
498   * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se23/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.1.2 Java Language Specification, section
499   * 9.1.2
500   */
501  public default boolean generic(final Element e) {
502    return switch (e) {
503    case null -> throw new NullPointerException("e");
504    case UniversalElement ue -> ue.generic();
505    case Parameterizable p -> {
506      try (var lock = this.lock()) {
507        yield switch (e.getKind()) {
508        case CLASS, CONSTRUCTOR, ENUM, INTERFACE, METHOD, RECORD -> !p.getTypeParameters().isEmpty();
509        default -> false;
510        };
511      }
512    }
513    default -> false;
514    };
515  }

1041   *
1042   * @param name the {@link CharSequence} to convert; may be {@code null} in which case {@code null} will be returned
1043   *
1044   * @return a {@link String}, or {@code null} if {@code name} was {@code null}
1045   *
1046   * @see #lock()
1047   */
1048  public default String toString(final CharSequence name) {
1049    return switch (name) {
1050    case null -> null;
1051    case String s -> s;
1052    case StringName sn -> sn.value();
1053    case Name n -> {
1054      try (var lock = this.lock()) {
1055        yield n.toString();
1056      }
1057    }
1058    default -> name.toString();
1059    };
1060  }

1181  /**
1182   * Returns the {@link TypeParameterElement} {@linkplain Parameterizable#getTypeParameters() contained} by the supplied
1183   * {@link Parameterizable} whose {@linkplain TypeParameterElement#getSimpleName() name} {@linkplain
1184   * Name#contentEquals(CharSequence) is equal to} the supplied {@code name}, <strong>or {@code null} if there is no
1185   * such {@link TypeParameterElement}</strong>.
1186   *
1187   * @param p a {@link Parameterizable}; must not be {@code null}
1188   *
1189   * @param name a name valid for a type parameter; must not be {@code null}
1190   *
1191   * @return a {@link TypeParameterElement}, or {@code null}
1192   */
1193  public default TypeParameterElement typeParameterElement(Parameterizable p, final CharSequence name) {
1194    Objects.requireNonNull(p, "p");
1195    Objects.requireNonNull(name, "name");
1196    while (p != null) {
1197      switch (p) {
1198      case UniversalElement ue:
1199        for (final UniversalElement tpe : ue.getTypeParameters()) {
1200          if (tpe.getSimpleName().contentEquals(name)) {
1201            return tpe;
1202          }
1203        }
1204        p = ue.getEnclosingElement();
1205        break;
1206      default:
1207        try (var lock = this.lock()) {
1208          for (final TypeParameterElement tpe : p.getTypeParameters()) {
1209            if (tpe.getSimpleName().contentEquals(name)) {
1210              return tpe;
1211            }
1212          }
1213          p = (Parameterizable)((Element)p).getEnclosingElement();
1214        }
1215        break;
1216      }
1217    }
1218    return null;
1219  }

1244   * that the supplied {@code enclosingElement} {@linkplain Element#getEnclosedElements() encloses}, <strong>or {@code
1245   * null} if there is no such {@link VariableElement}</strong>.

1248   *
1249   * @param simpleName a {@link CharSequence}; must not be {@code null}

1254   *
1255   * @see Element#getEnclosedElements()
1256   *
1257   * @see ElementKind#isVariable()
1258   *
1259   * @see Element#getSimpleName()
1260   *
1261   * @see VariableElement
1262   */
1263  public default VariableElement variableElement(final Element enclosingElement, final CharSequence simpleName) {
1264    Objects.requireNonNull(simpleName, "simpleName");
1265    return switch (enclosingElement) {
1266    case null -> throw new NullPointerException("enclosingElement");
1267    case UniversalElement ue -> {
1268      for (final UniversalElement ee : ue.getEnclosedElements()) {
1269        if (ee.getKind().isVariable() && ee.getSimpleName().contentEquals(simpleName)) {
1270          yield ee;
1271        }
1272      }
1273      yield null;
1274    }
1275    default -> {
1276      try (var lock = lock()) {
1277        for (final Element ee : enclosingElement.getEnclosedElements()) {
1278          if (ee.getKind().isVariable() && ee.getSimpleName().contentEquals(simpleName)) {
1279            yield (VariableElement)ee;
1280          }
1281        }
1282      }
1283      yield null;
1284    }
1285    };
